{
  "stem": "12462.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He remained head of the Documentation Division, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I believe, up until January of 1946.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But meanwhile, just before the trial begin-- began in November, maybe three weeks beforehand, Justice Jackson made him the chief of a kind of a review group of top officers.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was not on the group, and-- but we reported to that group now and then.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and Jackson liked the way Storey handled people so well that, all of a sudden, he was announced to be executive trial counsel, and that was before the trial started.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Storey actually had-- after Justice Jackson made his opening statement, his famous opening statement on November 21, 1945, Storey took over and indicated the manner in which we hoped to present documents.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It turned out to have a lot of flaws in it, but-- because we didn't have enough translations, and enough translations into French and into Russian, particularly.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this caused a great consternation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the tribunal stood up and said through Justice-- through President Lawrence, I don't want any documents put in here which are not in the language of all three of the other languages than German.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what happened was that we had to read the documents we were putting into evidence, and they would be interpreted simultaneously into French and into Russian and English.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if the document happened to be a French document, why, it'd be the-- into the other three languages, of course.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It had to be translated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, if it was translated, if a document was translated into the-- all the working languages of the court, you could introduce the document, assuming it was relevant.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But if it wasn't, you had to read from the document, and that slowed the proceedings down.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
